=== Etymology ===
From French ''hélicoptére'' which in turn comes from Greek ''heliko'' "helix, spiral" and ''pteron'' meaning "wing".

== [[noun]] ==
#an aircraft that is borne along by long rotating blades which allow it to hover, move or land, and a smaller set of blades on the tail part which stabilize the aircraft.
#:''We flew over the city on a helicopter''.

